{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17609137","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17609137"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:41:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:41:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16086"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16086","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16086"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.35,0.15,0,0.35]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8777"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74574"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8777","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8777"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16086"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60066"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"8576"},{"type":"tags","id":"8592"},{"type":"tags","id":"8595"},{"type":"tags","id":"10615"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20962"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20964"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74574","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74574"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe early stages of human embryonic development involve critical changes to the structure of the blastocyst as it prepares for implantation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes when the cytotrophoblast first forms during early embryonic development?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Day 4-5 post-fertilisation during morula formation","Day 8-9 post-fertilisation during implantation","Day 10-11 post-fertilisation during gastrulation","Day 2-3 post-fertilisation during cleavage","Day 6-7 post-fertilisation during blastocyst differentiation"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecytotrophoblast forms at day 6-7 post-fertilisation\u003C/strong\u003E when the trophoblast layer of the blastocyst differentiates into two distinct cell layers. This occurs just before implantation begins.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options represent incorrect timing:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDay 2-3 post-fertilisation during cleavage\u003C/strong\u003E - This is too early; the embryo is still undergoing cell division without differentiation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDay 4-5 post-fertilisation during morula formation\u003C/strong\u003E - The cells are compacting but have not yet differentiated into distinct layers\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDay 8-9 post-fertilisation during implantation\u003C/strong\u003E - The cytotrophoblast has already formed by this stage and is actively participating in implantation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDay 10-11 post-fertilisation during gastrulation\u003C/strong\u003E - This is far too late; the trophoblast layers are well-established by this point\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe cytotrophoblast forms the inner layer of the trophoblast and consists of individual stem cells that will continue to divide and fuse to form and maintain the outer syncytiotrophoblast layer throughout pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The cytotrophoblast forms at day 6-7 post-fertilisation when the trophoblast differentiates into two distinct layers.","The trophoblast is the outer layer of the blastocyst that will eventually form the placenta.","The cytotrophoblast is the inner layer of trophoblast cells that gives rise to the syncytiotrophoblast through cell fusion."],"references":["Lawless L, Qin Y, Xie L, Zhang K. Trophoblast Differentiation: Mechanisms and Implications for Pregnancy Complications. Nutrients. 2023 Aug 12;15(16):3564. doi: 10.3390/nu15163564. PMID: 37630754; PMCID: PMC10459728.","Zhou Y, Fisher SJ, Janatpour M, Genbacev O, Dejana E, Wheelock M, Damsky CH. Human cytotrophoblasts adopt a vascular phenotype as they differentiate. A strategy for successful endovascular invasion? J Clin Invest. 1997 May 1;99(9):2139-51. doi: 10.1172/JCI119387. PMID: 9151786; PMCID: PMC508044.","Wang Y, Zhao S. Vascular Biology of the Placenta. San Rafael (CA): Morgan \u0026 Claypool Life Sciences; 2010. Chapter 4, Cell Types of the Placenta. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK53245/","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60066"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16086"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60066","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60066"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-25T07:51:23+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-25T08:20:06+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8777"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74574"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups",